## 📘 Documentation

### Setup Process

1. Install Node.js and MongoDB
2. Go to backend folder and run:
   npm install
   node app.js
3. Open frontend using Live Server

The backend runs on `http://localhost:5000` and frontend runs on `http://127.0.0.1:5500`.

---

### API Explanation

* **GET /api/transactions**
  Fetch all transactions from database

* **POST /api/transactions**
  Add a new transaction (title, amount, type)

* **DELETE /api/transactions/:id**
  Delete a transaction using its ID

---

### Assumptions Made

* Only one admin user is used (no multi-user system)
* Authentication is handled using localStorage (for simplicity)
* Data is stored locally in MongoDB

---

### Trade-offs

* Did not implement full JWT authentication to keep the project simple
* No user registration system added
* Focus was on core functionality and clean UI instead of complex architecture

